.TH "drm_gem_cma_dumb_create_internal" 9 "drm_gem_cma_dumb_create_internal" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_gem_cma_dumb_create_internal \- create a dumb buffer object
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_gem_cma_dumb_create_internal
.BI "(struct drm_file *file_priv "  ","
.BI "struct drm_device *drm "  ","
.BI "struct drm_mode_create_dumb *args "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "file_priv" 12
DRM file-private structure to create the dumb buffer for
.IP "drm" 12
DRM device
.IP "args" 12
IOCTL data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This aligns the pitch and size arguments to the minimum required. This is
an internal helper that can be wrapped by a driver to account for hardware
with more specific alignment requirements. It should not be used directly
as their \fIdrm_driver.dumb_create\fP callback.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or a negative error code on failure.
